## Code Style & Conventions

### General
- Use **TypeScript** strictly вЂ” no `any`, no implicit `any`
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`
- Use named exports for components, default exports only for pages
- File names: `kebab-case` for files/folders, `PascalCase` for components
- Keep components small and focused вЂ” split when a file exceeds ~150 lines
- Write self-documenting code; add JSDoc only for non-obvious logic

### Next.js App Router
- Prefer **Server Components** by default; add `"use client"` only when needed
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` in every route segment
- Fetch data in Server Components using tRPC server-side caller
- Never fetch data inside Client Components directly вЂ” use TanStack Query
- Use `next/image` for all images, `next/font` for fonts
- Route groups: `(dashboard)`, `(auth)`, `(public)` for layout isolation



### Mongoose & Database
- Models in `src/server/models/` (User, Account, Session, Client, Project, Invoice, Payment)
- Use `getDb()` before any model query to ensure connection
- Use transactions for multi-document writes when needed
- All queries scoped to `userId` (ObjectId) for tenant isolation
- Soft-delete pattern: use `deletedAt Date?` instead of hard deletes
- Enum values: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE in schemas, map to camelCase in app

### Zustand
- One store per domain: `useClientStore`, `useProjectStore`, `useInvoiceStore`
- Store files in `src/stores/`
- Use `immer` middleware for nested state updates
- Keep stores minimal вЂ” only truly global UI state (not server data)

### Tailwind & UI
- Use shadcn/ui components as base; extend, don't override internals
- Use CSS variables for theme tokens (`--primary`, `--background`, etc.)
- Dark mode support required on all new components
- RTL support: use `rtl:` prefix utilities for Arabic layout
- Never use inline styles; never write raw CSS outside of `globals.css`

### AI / Gemini
- All AI calls go through `src/lib/ai/` вЂ” never call Gemini directly in components
- Always stream responses for long-form generation (email drafts, summaries)
- Include user context (client name, project data) in system prompts
- Cap token usage: `max_tokens: 1000` for short outputs, `2000` for documents
- Handle rate limit errors gracefully with retry logic (exponential backoff)

### Whop
- Use Whop Connect for payment processing (freelancer receives funds)

### BullMQ Jobs
- Define all jobs in `src/jobs/`
- Job names: `invoice:reminder`, `report:generate`, `email:send`
- Always handle job failures and set `attempts: 3` with backoff
- Log job start/end/failure to audit log

