## Architecture Rules

### Multi-tenancy
- Every DB query must be scoped to `userId` or `organizationId`
- Never fetch data without a where clause on tenant ID
- Use Supabase RLS as a safety net, not as the primary guard

### Error Handling
- Use typed errors: never throw raw strings
- API errors return `{ error: string, code: string }` with appropriate HTTP status
- Client-side: always show user-friendly messages, log technical details to Sentry
- Use `tryCatch` wrapper in service layer

### Environment Variables
- All secrets in `.env.local` (never committed)
- Validate env vars at startup using Zod in `src/env.ts`
- Prefix browser-safe vars with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`


### Security
- Validate ALL user inputs with Zod before touching the DB
- Rate limit: 100 req/min per IP, 1000 req/min per Pro account
- Use `bcrypt` (cost 12) for any password hashing
- CORS: whitelist only known domains
- Audit log: track all sensitive actions (invoice created, payment recorded, etc.)
- GDPR: implement data export + erasure endpoints

